function foo(x: int): int {
  if (x == 0) {
    return 1;
  } else {
    return x * foo(x - 1);
  }
}

function main(): void {
  echo foo(5);
}

This code will produce a stack overflow error for large values of x.  The recursive calls to foo consume excessive stack space. This is a common issue in recursive functions when not implemented carefully.